[{"text": "This is our Universe,", "start": 6.039, "duration": 3.07}, {"text": "an ever-expanding network of stars", "start": 9.109, "duration": 3.169}, {"text": "and galaxies.", "start": 12.278, "duration": 1.502}, {"text": "And this is your brain.", "start": 13.78, "duration": 3.87}, {"text": "Don\u2019t they look eerily", "start": 17.65, "duration": 2.37}, {"text": "similar to one another?", "start": 20.02, "duration": 2.902}, {"text": "Your brain is made up of neurons.", "start": 45.178, "duration": 3.07}, {"text": "These are cells that process", "start": 48.248, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "information and signals", "start": 50.25, "duration": 1.635}, {"text": "throughout your body.", "start": 51.885, "duration": 1.368}, {"text": "Between these neurons", "start": 53.253, "duration": 1.802}, {"text": "is an underlying network of connections", "start": 55.055, "duration": 3.036}, {"text": "that allows them", "start": 58.091, "duration": 0.834}, {"text": "to communicate with each other.", "start": 58.925, "duration": 2.269}, {"text": "And on the largest scale imaginable,", "start": 61.194, "duration": 3.503}, {"text": "the galaxies in our Universe ", "start": 64.697, "duration": 2.636}, {"text": "form clusters with vast", "start": 67.333, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "amounts of empty space in between.", "start": 69.502, "duration": 2.67}, {"text": "These clusters are connected", "start": 72.172, "duration": 1.902}, {"text": "to each other by a complex network", "start": 74.074, "duration": 2.168}, {"text": "known as cosmic webs.", "start": 76.242, "duration": 2.503}, {"text": "The Universe and your brain.", "start": 78.745, "duration": 3.637}, {"text": "Puzzling, isn\u2019t it?", "start": 82.382, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "Well, maybe our Universe is", "start": 84.384, "duration": 2.536}, {"text": "a lot more complex than we thought.", "start": 86.92, "duration": 2.936}, {"text": "It might just be some sort of", "start": 89.856, "duration": 2.769}, {"text": "giant brain.", "start": 92.625, "duration": 3.404}, {"text": "Digging into these concepts can be challenging,", "start": 96.029, "duration": 3.537}, {"text": "and sometimes I need help breaking things down", "start": 99.566, "duration": 2.836}, {"text": "so I can understand them better.", "start": 102.402, "duration": 1.868}, {"text": "Well, that\u2019s why I use Blinkist.", "start": 104.27, "duration": 2.369}, {"text": "Blinkist is an app that allows you to understand", "start": 106.639, "duration": 2.636}, {"text": "the most critical ideas from over 5,500 non-fiction books and podcasts", "start": 109.275, "duration": 5.806}, {"text": "in an exceptional audio experience.", "start": 115.081, "duration": 2.469}, {"text": "In just 15 minutes, you can listen to powerful insights", "start": 117.55, "duration": 3.504}, {"text": "into mindblowing topics from over 27 categories.", "start": 121.054, "duration": 4.137}, {"text": "Right now, I\u2019m checking out Futures with Robert Mason.", "start": 125.191, "duration": 3.604}, {"text": "It dives deep into the developments that might drastically", "start": 128.795, "duration": 3.637}, {"text": "alter what it means to be human. ", "start": 132.432, "duration": 2.436}, {"text": "And with the new Blinkist Connect feature,", "start": 134.868, "duration": 2.969}, {"text": "you can share a subscription with a premium account. ", "start": 137.837, "duration": 3.203}, {"text": "So when you\u2019re reading about the mysteries of the Universe", "start": 141.04, "duration": 2.603}, {"text": "or unique marketing strategies,", "start": 143.643, "duration": 2.202}, {"text": "you can share these insights with your best friend.", "start": 145.845, "duration": 2.936}, {"text": "That\u2019s two premium accounts for the price of one!", "start": 148.781, "duration": 2.837}, {"text": "So let\u2019s find new inspirations together.", "start": 151.618, "duration": 3.67}, {"text": "Get a 7-day free trial at blinkist.com/whatif.", "start": 155.288, "duration": 4.037}, {"text": "Sign up now and get 25% off!", "start": 159.325, "duration": 2.77}, {"text": "If you\u2019re lucky, maybe the Universe will share\nits subscription with you.", "start": 162.095, "duration": 4.905}, {"text": "Now, you could be thinking,", "start": 167.0, "duration": 3.103}, {"text": "wow, What If has really gone off the rails", "start": 170.103, "duration": 2.936}, {"text": "with this episode.", "start": 173.039, "duration": 0.968}, {"text": "This guy is crazy.", "start": 174.007, "duration": 2.035}, {"text": "But we\u2019re not the only ones to notice", "start": 176.042, "duration": 2.336}, {"text": "the similarities between", "start": 178.378, "duration": 1.168}, {"text": "galaxies in the cosmos and neurons", "start": 179.546, "duration": 2.736}, {"text": "in the human brain.", "start": 182.282, "duration": 1.468}, {"text": "Astrophysicists and neurosurgeons", "start": 183.75, "duration": 3.103}, {"text": "have been studying these networks.", "start": 186.853, "duration": 2.402}, {"text": "And they found that the cosmos looks", "start": 189.255, "duration": 3.537}, {"text": "very similar to your brain,", "start": 192.792, "duration": 3.237}, {"text": "just on a much larger scale.", "start": 196.029, "duration": 3.837}, {"text": "Your brain is 77% water.", "start": 199.866, "duration": 3.603}, {"text": "And the cosmic web is about ", "start": 203.469, "duration": 2.436}, {"text": "73% dark energy.", "start": 205.905, "duration": 4.071}, {"text": "There are around", "start": 209.976, "duration": 1.201}, {"text": "69 billion neurons in your brain.", "start": 211.177, "duration": 3.57}, {"text": "And the cosmic web could connect", "start": 214.747, "duration": 2.47}, {"text": "at least 100 billion galaxies.", "start": 217.217, "duration": 3.636}, {"text": "Not exactly the same.", "start": 220.853, "duration": 1.602}, {"text": "But not too far off either.", "start": 222.455, "duration": 3.937}, {"text": "Wait, there\u2019s more.", "start": 226.392, "duration": 2.536}, {"text": "Neurons and galaxies", "start": 228.928, "duration": 1.835}, {"text": "both share a similar pattern.", "start": 230.763, "duration": 2.236}, {"text": "2.5 mm (0.1 in) of your brain", "start": 232.999, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "looks like 500 million light-years of space.", "start": 235.168, "duration": 4.404}, {"text": "Pretty cool, right?", "start": 239.572, "duration": 1.969}, {"text": "Well, even that isn\u2019t all.", "start": 241.541, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "Each neuron", "start": 243.476, "duration": 1.235}, {"text": "of that 2.5 mm (0.1 in) of your brain", "start": 244.711, "duration": 2.435}, {"text": "connects to about five other neurons.", "start": 247.146, "duration": 3.504}, {"text": "And in space,", "start": 250.65, "duration": 1.602}, {"text": "each galaxy has about", "start": 252.252, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "four different connections.", "start": 254.187, "duration": 2.502}, {"text": "Your brain and the cosmos aren\u2019t identical.", "start": 256.689, "duration": 3.604}, {"text": "But they are similar enough", "start": 260.293, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "for you to ask this.", "start": 262.462, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": "Could it have its own consciousness?", "start": 268.768, "duration": 4.905}, {"text": "Theoretically, the Universe", "start": 273.673, "duration": 2.069}, {"text": "could achieve consciousness.", "start": 275.742, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "But only if it managed", "start": 277.677, "duration": 2.235}, {"text": "to understand", "start": 279.912, "duration": 1.102}, {"text": "its position in space and time.", "start": 281.014, "duration": 2.769}, {"text": "Then it would need to understand", "start": 283.783, "duration": 2.336}, {"text": "how it relates", "start": 286.119, "duration": 1.434}, {"text": "to other things, like you.", "start": 287.553, "duration": 2.67}, {"text": "Have I blown your mind yet?", "start": 290.223, "duration": 2.769}, {"text": "Now, the Universe isn\u2019t", "start": 292.992, "duration": 2.202}, {"text": "exactly like your brain.", "start": 295.194, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "It\u2019s a lot harder for it", "start": 296.929, "duration": 2.069}, {"text": "to exchange information", "start": 298.998, "duration": 1.535}, {"text": "between the galaxies.", "start": 300.533, "duration": 1.568}, {"text": "It might be conscious,", "start": 302.101, "duration": 2.236}, {"text": "but on a level we don\u2019t yet understand.", "start": 304.337, "duration": 4.338}, {"text": "And how could we understand", "start": 308.675, "duration": 2.402}, {"text": "the consciousness of our Universe", "start": 311.077, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "if we don\u2019t even fully", "start": 312.812, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "know what consciousness is", "start": 314.981, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "and how it works?", "start": 316.716, "duration": 2.235}, {"text": "What we do know", "start": 318.951, "duration": 1.168}, {"text": "is that your own consciousness", "start": 320.119, "duration": 2.036}, {"text": "is pretty advanced.", "start": 322.155, "duration": 1.968}, {"text": "All thanks to your ability", "start": 324.123, "duration": 1.602}, {"text": "to understand what the future is.", "start": 325.725, "duration": 4.605}, {"text": "Humans are one of the few animals", "start": 330.33, "duration": 2.635}, {"text": "that think about tomorrow.", "start": 332.965, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "At least as far as we know.", "start": 335.134, "duration": 2.403}, {"text": "But maybe we overcomplicate things.", "start": 337.537, "duration": 2.669}, {"text": "Maybe consciousness", "start": 340.206, "duration": 1.368}, {"text": "isn\u2019t an intricate biological thing", "start": 341.574, "duration": 2.569}, {"text": "only humans have.", "start": 344.143, "duration": 1.435}, {"text": "Maybe consciousness", "start": 345.578, "duration": 2.136}, {"text": "is when systems relate to each other", "start": 347.714, "duration": 3.003}, {"text": "and work together.", "start": 350.717, "duration": 1.568}, {"text": "Like the Universe.", "start": 352.285, "duration": 2.569}, {"text": "Then, yes,", "start": 354.854, "duration": 1.201}, {"text": "the Universe is conscious.", "start": 356.055, "duration": 2.102}, {"text": "Especially if", "start": 358.157, "duration": 1.202}, {"text": "you think of the Universe with its", "start": 359.359, "duration": 1.601}, {"text": "billions of galaxies,", "start": 360.96, "duration": 2.069}, {"text": "billions upon billions of star systems,", "start": 363.029, "duration": 3.403}, {"text": "planets, moons.", "start": 366.432, "duration": 3.604}, {"text": "That\u2019s a lot of consciousness.", "start": 370.036, "duration": 2.869}, {"text": "Maybe there are other universes,", "start": 372.905, "duration": 2.603}, {"text": "living on a much larger scale,", "start": 375.508, "duration": 2.135}, {"text": "communicating with each other", "start": 377.643, "duration": 1.368}, {"text": "like we do.", "start": 379.011, "duration": 1.402}, {"text": "And maybe they collide.", "start": 380.413, "duration": 3.337}, {"text": "Well, that\u2019s a story for another WHAT IF.", "start": 383.75, "duration": 5.372}]